<p><b>3. <u><font color="#006699">A BRIEF RECAP OF THE &quot;OLD RULES&quot; CAPITAL GAINS TAXES</font></u></b></p>

<p><u><b><font size="3">Taxpayers in either the 10% or 15% income tax bracket </font><font
size="4"><em>ONLY</em></font><font size="3">:</font></b></u> 

<!--mstheme--></font><!--msthemelist--><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
	<!--msthemelist--><tr><td valign="baseline" width="42"><img src="_themes/sanderscpa/aradbul1.gif" width="15" height="15" hspace="13" alt="bullet"></td><td valign="top" width="100%"><!--mstheme--><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">After 1/1/2001, taxpayers will be subject to the current capital gains tax rate of 10%
    on assets held from 12 to 60 months, OR the 8% rate on &quot;super long term&quot; assets
    held more than 60 months.<!--mstheme--></font><!--msthemelist--></td></tr>
<!--msthemelist--></table><!--mstheme--><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">

<p><font size="3"><u><b>Taxpayers in income tax brackets above 15%:</b></u></font> 

<!--mstheme--></font><!--msthemelist--><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
	<!--msthemelist--><tr><td valign="baseline" width="42"><img src="_themes/sanderscpa/aradbul1.gif" width="15" height="15" hspace="13" alt="bullet"></td><td valign="top" width="100%"><!--mstheme--><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Capital gains tax on assets held over 12 months will be 20%, the same as it has been
    since 1/1/1998, except for certain assets purchased after 1/1/2001, or on assets where the
    specific tax election is made as of 1/1/2001 and the tax paid at that time.<!--mstheme--></font><!--msthemelist--></td></tr>
	<!--msthemelist--><tr><td valign="baseline" width="42"><img src="_themes/sanderscpa/aradbul1.gif" width="15" height="15" hspace="13" alt="bullet"></td><td valign="top" width="100%"><!--mstheme--><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">The lower 18% &quot;super long term&quot; capital gains rate is <u>NOT EVER</u>
    available for <u>ANY</u> asset acquired before 12/31/2000, UNLESS the election to report
    the gain in market value as of 1/1/2001 is made, AND the capital gains taxes are paid at
    that time on any appreciation, AND the asset is then held for another 60 months after
    1/1/2001, which means 1/1/2006 is the earliest possible qualifying date.<!--mstheme--></font><!--msthemelist--></td></tr>
	<!--msthemelist--><tr><td valign="baseline" width="42"><img src="_themes/sanderscpa/aradbul1.gif" width="15" height="15" hspace="13" alt="bullet"></td><td valign="top" width="100%"><!--mstheme--><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Assets purchased after 1/1/2001, which are then held for 60 months are eligible for the
    lower 18% &quot;super long term&quot; capital gains tax rate, so the earliest date a sale
    can qualify for the 18% rate is 1/1/2006.<!--mstheme--></font><!--msthemelist--></td></tr>
<!--msthemelist--></table><!--mstheme--><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">
